<i>bound noun</i>: 판 [판], 통 [통], 턱 [턱], 터 [터], 지경 [지경] <i>noun</i>: 환경 [환경], 형편 [형편], 형세 [형세], 형국 [형국], 풍토 [풍토], 풍경 [풍경], 푼수 [푼ː수], 판세 [판쎄], 판국 [판국], 정세 [정세], 입장 [입짱], 위치 [위치], 외형 [외ː형/웨ː형], 영문 [영문], 앞뒤 [압뛰], 상황 [상황], 사태 [사ː태], 사정 [사ː정], 배경 [배ː경], 모양새 [모양새], 노릇 [노륻], 국면 [궁면], 경황 [경황] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>bound noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>판 [판]</dt><br>
<dd>1. situation</dd><br>
<dd>처해 있는 상황이나 형편.</dd><br>
<dd>The situation or circumstances that one faces.</dd><br>
<dd>2. round; game</dd><br>
<dd>승부를 겨루는 일을 세는 단위.</dd><br>
<dd>A unit to count the number of games one won or lost.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>통 [통]</dt><br>
<dd>situation</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일이 벌어진 상황이나 형편.</dd><br>
<dd>A bound noun used to indicate a situation or circumstances of a certain incident.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>턱 [턱]</dt><br>
<dd>1. reason; cause</dd><br>
<dd>그렇게 되어야 할 까닭이나 이유.</dd><br>
<dd>A bound noun meaning a reason or cause that explains why something must be that way.</dd><br>
<dd>2. level; situation</dd><br>
<dd>그만한 정도나 처지.</dd><br>
<dd>A bound noun meaning such a degree or situation.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>터 [터]</dt><br>
<dd>1. (no equivalent expression)</dd><br>
<dd>예정이나 추측, 의지를 나타내는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>A bound noun meaning one’s plan, guess, or will.</dd><br>
<dd>2. position; situation</dd><br>
<dd>처지나 상황.</dd><br>
<dd>A bound noun meaning one’s situation or circumstances.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>지경 [지경]</dt><br>
<dd>situation</dd><br>
<dd>경우, 형편, 정도 등의 뜻을 나타내는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>A bound noun used to indicate a case, condition, level, etc.</dd><br>
</li>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>환경 [환경]</dt><br>
<dd>1. environment</dd><br>
<dd>생물이 살아가는 데 영향을 주는 자연 상태나 조건.</dd><br>
<dd>The state of nature affecting the life of living creatures.</dd><br>
<dd>2. condition; situation; circumstances</dd><br>
<dd>인간에게 영향을 주는 주위의 조건이나 상황.</dd><br>
<dd>The condition or situation of the surroundings affecting humans.</dd><br>
<dd>3. environment; situation</dd><br>
<dd>인간이 생활하는 주위의 상태.</dd><br>
<dd>The state of surroundings in which a person is living.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>형편 [형편]</dt><br>
<dd>1. situation; state</dd><br>
<dd>일이 되어 가는 상황.</dd><br>
<dd>The progress or unfolding of a certain event.</dd><br>
<dd>2. situation; condition; circumstances</dd><br>
<dd>살림살이의 상태나 처지.</dd><br>
<dd>The economic situation or condition of one's life.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>형세 [형세]</dt><br>
<dd>1. condition; circumstances; situation</dd><br>
<dd>살림살이의 형편.</dd><br>
<dd>The financial condition of one's life.</dd><br>
<dd>2. situation; circumstances</dd><br>
<dd>일이 되어 가는 형편.</dd><br>
<dd>A situation or state in which things are shaping up.</dd><br>
<dd>3. vigor; force; spirit</dd><br>
<dd>힘차게 뻗치는 기운이나 세력.</dd><br>
<dd>Vigor or vitality that extends strongly.</dd><br>
<dd>4. shape; geographical feature</dd><br>
<dd>풍수지리에서, 산의 모양이나 지형.</dd><br>
<dd>A mountain's shape or geography in Korea's system of geomancy, or feng shui.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>형국 [형국]</dt><br>
<dd>situation; state</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일이 벌어진 형편이나 상황.</dd><br>
<dd>The situation or circumstances under which a certain event takes place.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>풍토 [풍토]</dt><br>
<dd>1. climate; natural features</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 지역의 기후와 토지의 상태.</dd><br>
<dd>The climate and land condition of a certain region.</dd><br>
<dd>2. environment; situation</dd><br>
<dd>(비유적으로) 어떤 일의 바탕이 되는 제도나 조건.</dd><br>
<dd>(figurative) Rules or conditions, as the foundation of something.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>풍경 [풍경]</dt><br>
<dd>1. scenery; scene; view</dd><br>
<dd>자연이나 지역의 아름다운 모습.</dd><br>
<dd>A beautiful scene of nature or an area.</dd><br>
<dd>2. scene; situation</dd><br>
<dd>감정을 불러일으키는 경치나 상황.</dd><br>
<dd>A special scene or situation that evokes an emotion.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>푼수 [푼ː수]</dt><br>
<dd>1. situation; state</dd><br>
<dd>상태나 형편.</dd><br>
<dd>One's situation or state.</dd><br>
<dd>2. idiot</dd><br>
<dd>(놀리는 말로) 생각이 모자라고 어리석은 사람.</dd><br>
<dd>(teasing) A slow-witted, stupid person.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>판세 [판쎄]</dt><br>
<dd>situation; condition of affairs</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일이 되어 가는 판의 형세.</dd><br>
<dd>The status in the progress of a certain project.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>판국 [판국]</dt><br>
<dd>situation; state of affairs</dd><br>
<dd>일이 벌어져 있는 상황이나 상태.</dd><br>
<dd>The situation or state of a certain incident in progress.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>정세 [정세]</dt><br>
<dd>situation</dd><br>
<dd>일이 되어 가는 형편.</dd><br>
<dd>A situation where something unfolds.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>입장 [입짱]</dt><br>
<dd>position; situation; standpoint; ground; stance</dd><br>
<dd>바로 눈앞에 처하고 있는 처지나 상황. 또는 그런 처지에 대한 태도.</dd><br>
<dd>The state or situation one faces at the moment, or the attitude one takes in this position.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>위치 [위치]</dt><br>
<dd>1. location; situation</dd><br>
<dd>일정한 곳에 자리를 차지함. 또는 그 자리.</dd><br>
<dd>The state of having taken up space in a place; such space.</dd><br>
<dd>2. position; place</dd><br>
<dd>사회적으로 담당하고 있는 지위나 역할.</dd><br>
<dd>A position or role that one occupies or plays in society.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>외형 [외ː형/웨ː형]</dt><br>
<dd>1. appearance; shape; form</dd><br>
<dd>사물의 겉모양.</dd><br>
<dd>The outer appearance of an object.</dd><br>
<dd>2. situation; circumstances</dd><br>
<dd>겉으로 드러난 형편.</dd><br>
<dd>The circumstances revealed outwardly.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>영문 [영문]</dt><br>
<dd>reason; situation</dd><br>
<dd>일이 되어 가는 상태나 이유.</dd><br>
<dd>The state or cause of a matter.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>앞뒤 [압뛰]</dt><br>
<dd>1. front and back; forward and backward direction</dd><br>
<dd>앞과 뒤.</dd><br>
<dd>The front and back.</dd><br>
<dd>2. the time before and after; situation; context</dd><br>
<dd>먼저와 나중.</dd><br>
<dd>The earlier and later time.</dd><br>
<dd>3. context; earlier and later statements</dd><br>
<dd>앞말과 뒷말.</dd><br>
<dd>The words said earlier and later.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>상황 [상황]</dt><br>
<dd>situation; condition</dd><br>
<dd>일이 진행되어 가는 형편이나 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>The stiuation or state of how something is proceeding.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>사태 [사ː태]</dt><br>
<dd>situation; state</dd><br>
<dd>일이 되어 가는 상황이나 벌어진 일의 상태.</dd><br>
<dd>A progress or unfolding of a certain event, or a state of things that happened.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>사정 [사ː정]</dt><br>
<dd>1. situation; circumstances</dd><br>
<dd>일의 형편이나 이유.</dd><br>
<dd>The situation or reason for an incident.</dd><br>
<dd>2. pleading; begging</dd><br>
<dd>다른 사람에게 일의 형편을 말하고 도와줄 것을 부탁함.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of explaining the situation of something to someone and asking for his/her help.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>배경 [배ː경]</dt><br>
<dd>1. background</dd><br>
<dd>뒤쪽의 경치.</dd><br>
<dd>The view at the back.</dd><br>
<dd>2. background; situation</dd><br>
<dd>사건이나 사람 등과 관계있는 주변 상황.</dd><br>
<dd>The surrounding circumstances related to a certain incident or person</dd><br>
<dd>3. backing; support</dd><br>
<dd>뒤에서 받쳐 주는 힘이나 조건.</dd><br>
<dd>A power or condition that supports a person behind him/her.</dd><br>
<dd>4. setting; background; backdrop</dd><br>
<dd>문학 작품에서, 시간적, 공간적, 사회적 환경.</dd><br>
<dd>A temporal, spatial, and social environment in literature.</dd><br>
<dd>5. background; backdrop</dd><br>
<dd>공연에서, 무대 뒤에 꾸며 놓은 장치.</dd><br>
<dd>A device installed at the back of a stage in a performance.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>모양새 [모양새]</dt><br>
<dd>1. outward appearance; look</dd><br>
<dd>사람이나 물건의 생긴 겉모습.</dd><br>
<dd>Outward appearance of a person or thing.</dd><br>
<dd>2. situation; state</dd><br>
<dd>(속된 말로) 일이 되어가는 형편이나 상태.</dd><br>
<dd>(slang) A situation or state in which things are shaping up.</dd><br>
<dd>3. honor; face</dd><br>
<dd>(속된 말로) 체면.</dd><br>
<dd>(slang) One's face or honor.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>노릇 [노륻]</dt><br>
<dd>1. job; work</dd><br>
<dd>(낮잡아 이르는 말로) 직업으로 하는 일이나 직책을 맡아 하는 역할.</dd><br>
<dd>(disparaging) What one does as his/her occupation; or a role assumed in line with his/her position.</dd><br>
<dd>2. role; part</dd><br>
<dd>역할에 어울리는 행동이나 태도.</dd><br>
<dd>Behavior or attitude that suits one's role.</dd><br>
<dd>3. situation; circumstances</dd><br>
<dd>일의 상황 또는 형편.</dd><br>
<dd>The situation or circumstances in which things are happening.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>국면 [궁면]</dt><br>
<dd>aspect of affairs; situation</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일이 진행되어 가는 상황.</dd><br>
<dd>A developing situation.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>경황 [경황]</dt><br>
<dd>state of things; situation</dd><br>
<dd>자세히 살펴볼 여유가 없는 급한 상황.</dd><br>
<dd>An urgent or busy situation without time to look around.</dd><br>
